From: Project Assistant <dev@himalacove.local>
Date: Mon, 20 Jul 2026 03:36:33 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(availability): replace simulated availability with
 inventory-based calculation

Phase 2A re-implementation, Milestone 4.

- lib/availability.ts: getAvailabilityStatus now computes real
  remaining units (room-inventory.ts unitCount minus overlapping,
  non-cancelled bookings from bookings.ts) instead of a deterministic
  hash simulation. Signature unchanged. hashString, calculateNights,
  calculateEstimatedTotal, validateSearchDates untouched.
- app/search/page.tsx: converted to an async Server Component that
  computes hasSearch/validation/nights/results server-side and passes
  them to SearchResultsContent as props. Added
  export const dynamic = "force-dynamic".
- components/search/search-results-content.tsx: now a props-driven
  Client Component (removed useSearchParams and the client-side
  useMemo computation). useRouter retained for the re-search bar and
  clear-filters action. All JSX/styling unchanged.

Necessary because a client bundle only has the bookings array snapshot
from build/hydration time and would never see reservations created via
the Milestone 2 Server Action -- moving computation server-side is
what makes results reflect real, current bookings.

Verified with npx tsc --noEmit, npm run lint (both clean), and a real
functional check (via npx tsx) against actual seed data: correct unit
counts, overlapping bookings reduce availability, unknown room ids
resolve to unavailable, cancelled bookings are excluded, and repeated
calls are deterministic.
